Package io.siv.support.annotation

Annotation Type Target

public @interface Target
Defines an environment for running cucumber tests against.

  • Optional Element Summary

    Optional Elements 
    Modifier and Type Optional Element Description
    boolean acceptSslCerts
    Use this capability to ignore invalid certificate error in your test.
    String appium
    Specifies what version of appium to use.
    String browser
    Specifies what browser to use.
    String browserName
    Specifies what browser to use.
    String browserVersion
    Specifies what browser version to use.
    String[] custom
    Use this to add properties not directly named by Target.
    String device
    Specifies a particular mobile device for the test environment.
    String os
    Specifies what operating system to use.
    String osVersion
    Specifies what variant of the operating system to use.
    boolean realMobile
    Use this flag to test on a physical mobile device.

  • Element Details

    • acceptSslCerts

      boolean acceptSslCerts
      Use this capability to ignore invalid certificate error in your test.
      Returns:
      boolean
      Default:
      true

    • browser

      String browser
      Specifies what browser to use.

      e.g Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge, IE

      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • browserName

      String browserName
      Specifies what browser to use. Only has effect when device is set.

      e.g iPhone, android

      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • browserVersion

      String browserVersion
      Specifies what browser version to use. When empty, BrowerStack picks for us.
      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • os

      String os
      Specifies what operating system to use.

      e.g. Windows, OS X

      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • osVersion

      String osVersion
      Specifies what variant of the operating system to use. When empty, BrowerStack picks for us.
      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • device

      String device
      Specifies a particular mobile device for the test environment.
      Returns:
      String
      Default:
      ""

    • realMobile

      boolean realMobile
      Use this flag to test on a physical mobile device. Only has effect when device is set.
      Returns:
      boolean
      Default:
      false

    • appium

      String appium
      Specifies what version of appium to use. Only has effect when device is set.

      In most cases, you should leave this empty and let BrowserStack pick the version.

      Returns:
      The appium version
      Default:
      ""

    • custom

      String[] custom
      Use this to add properties not directly named by Target.

      custom = "someBrowserStackProp=Xxx" or custom = { "someBrowserStackProp=Xxx", "someOtherBrowserStackProp=Xxx" }

      Returns:
      Array of Strings
      Default:
      {""}
